FBIS4-35848 "drnes108_v_94011" FBIS-NES-94-108 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 Pakistan Court Grants Bail for Mir Murtaza Bhutto Court Grants Bail for Mir Murtaza Bhutto BK0506120394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 1100 GMT 5 Jun 94 BK0506120394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network English BFN [Text] Mir Murtaza Bhutto, member of Sindh assembly and brother of Prime Minister Ms. Benazir Bhutto, was granted bail in Shah Bandar case by the special court for speedy trial consisting of Mr. Ali Ahmad Junejo in Karachi today. The court, while granting bail, directed Mir Murtaza Bhutto to furnish two sureties of 500,000 rupees each. It also bound him not to leave the country until the trial of the case is completed.
